When solving this problem, we must remember to apply the order of operations. First, we perform all cases of multiplication and division from left to right to obtain

\begin{align*}
1+6\cdot2-3+5\cdot4\div2&=1+12-3+5\cdot4\div2\\
&=1+12-3+20\div 2\\
&=1+12-3+10.
\end{align*}Next, we perform all the required additions and subtractions from left to right. We get  \begin{align*}
1+12-3+10&=13-3+10\\
&=10+10\\
&=\boxed{20}.
\end{align*}

Of the 40 who had heart trouble, 20 also had high blood pressure, so there are $40-20=20$ teachers who only have heart trouble.  Similarly, there are $70-20 =50$ teachers with only high blood pressure.  So, of the 120 teachers total, there are $20 + 20 + 50 = 90$ teachers with one of these two maladies.  That means $120-90 = 30$ teachers with neither, which is $\frac{30}{120} = \boxed{25\%}$ of the teachers.

